{
  "stem": "20142.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were about 16 youngsters from the Hashomer Hatzair organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were also many youngsters who volunteer, I mean youngsters-- the ages were between 19 and 25, that were connected with the families of the Hashomer Hatzair or were in bunkers hiding already or they were in certain industries that were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] employing Jews in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know if you are aware, but there was about 36,000 Jews in Warsaw in January and February and March, until the real uprising.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were working for Germany industry, like Tobbens, Schultz, and-- these were places which were making brooms, uniforms, and the others.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Precinct 1 one that was on Franciszkanska Street was Antek Zuckerman in command.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the communication of the-- between these places was not done by any telephone or telegram, but mouth-to-mouth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were using messengers, people who could rely on and delivering messages as they could, [INAUDIBLE] best knowledge.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had to know the routes, over the rooftops, underneath the ruins, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I participated in the messenger services between Antek Zuckerman bunker and Mila 18 of Mordechai Anielewicz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With the operation of the--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The minute we have seen that there's no opposition from the Germans, we directed the people to the gates of the homes and helping them carry whatever they had with them to make it as smooth operation as possible.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And once they got into homes, we knew the Germans would not follow them to recover any number of people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were no small children or anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were mostly adults in the ages of 25 to 35, mostly women.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the reason that they decided to go to Umschlagplatz, because the conditions of living in Warsaw ghetto was extremely difficult, for many reasons.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, the--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--operation--",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
